title: Antique French Paste Gilded Bar Brooch | Late 1800s Early 1900s Engraved Pin | Something Old Wedding Jewelry | Bridal Gift Idea
description:
Delicate antique French gilded engraved bar brooch with three prong set very shiny paste stones. This simple and elegant brooch is from the late 19th century or early 20th century. 
The closure is a typical C clasp. 
It is in good vintage condition considering its age. The pin at the back is slightly bent as it was often used to gather thick fabric. 
A wonderful "something old" gift for a wedding or a great addition to any antique collection. 

Dimensions: length 2 3/4"  width 1/8"

What is Paste? Paste is a special type of cut glass which emulates a variety of gemstones. In antique jewelry, lead glass was most used, since the denser the material, the higher the refractive index and the greater the dispersion.  
Paste jewelry dates to France during the 18th century when a jeweler named Georges Frederic Strass began hand crafting fine-quality Paste jewelry in 1724. He was quickly then appointed as “Jeweler to the King” and began making Paste jewelry for King Louis XV of France.  
The popularity of Paste jewelry quickly rocketed, with the appeal being that it was almost impossible to tell the difference between Paste and the real thing. In fact, in most cases Paste looked and sparkled better!  
Paste jewels were also often more labor intensive to craft than Gemstone jewelry, as the Paste glass had to be expertly cut and polished by hand. This made the appeal even greater with many in Parisian high society deeming Paste jewelry superior to the real thing!

We use a proprietary adhesive to screen print the design, then apply flock fibers for a high-end, raised look. Unlike painted or UV-printed mats, our flocked doormats resist fading and wear, ensuring longevity and durability.

PROOF APPROVAL NEEDED FOR CUSTOM ORDERS

IN A RUSH? You've come to the right place! Overnight shipping is available. Select "Rush" or "Overnight Shipping" and include the date you need it by in the note section at checkout.

PRODUCT FEATURES:
100% NATURAL COIR WITH PVC BACKING: The natural coconut fiber surface provides durability and traction, while the PVC rubber backing adds slip resistance.

VARIETY OF DESIGNS: We offer hundreds of designs and sayings to suit any entryway style or personality.

CUSTOM COLORS: The "design color" refers to the design/text printed on the doormat, not the mat itself. For an additional fee, we can color the entire doormat. Message us if you don't see the color you want! (Note: Colors may appear differently on various screens.)

PERFECT SIZE FOR ANY ENTRYWAY: Choose from one of our five standard sizes or request a custom cut! Available sizes: 18"x30", 24"x36", 24"x72", 36"x60", and 36"x72". For custom sizes, visit custom order link. https://doormatdecor.etsy.com/listing/970358882

For 18"x30" and 24"x36" orders, please request a proof in the note section at checkout, and I will be happy to provide one before production begins.

EASY TO CLEAN: Perfect for indoor and outdoor use—simply shake, vacuum, or sweep.

CARE INSTRUCTIONS:
Avoid Direct Sunlight or Excessive Moisture: Prolonged exposure may cause discoloration or damage. Best used in sheltered areas such as covered porches or entryways.

*MAT DARKENS WHEN WET* Avoid wetting only part of the mat to prevent uneven appearance. Do not place live potted plants next to the mat, as water can soak into it unevenly.
-Drying Tips: If the mat becomes saturated, allow it to dry completely before stepping on it again.
-Occasional Clay Pieces: You may find small clay pieces in the mat, which is normal and part of the manufacturing process.
-If you notice a ring around your doormat staining the concrete, it's not caused by the mat itself but by water and dirt buildup. To prevent this, we recommend purchasing a layering rug to place under your doormat.

*SHIPPING ADIVCE* When your package arrives, open it outside. Some flock fibers may come loose during transit. Carefully remove the mat and shake it gently (avoid vigorous shaking) as the mat is heavy and could tear if mishandled.

NOTE FOR INTERNATIONAL BUYERS:

Shipping to Puerto Rico, Hawaii, Alaska, and U.S. Virgin Islands may also incur additional charges.
